verbose_text: There were no significant correlations observed between changes in peak potassium levels at reperfusion and the following variables - potassium levels during reperfusion, preoperative MELD score, cold and warm ischemia times, potassium effluent levels of the donor liver, norepinephrine dose at the time of reperfusion, total norepinephrine use prior to reperfusion, and length of the anhepatic stage (XREF_TABLE).
